webpackJsonp([0xf89e19ac0e95],{465:function(a,s){a.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Jeffry.in",author:"Jeff Wainwright"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jwainwright/Dropbox/me/git-docs/yowainwright.github.io/src/pages/2016-05-19-creating-aliases-mac.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>Creating Aliases on a Mac is an easy thing to do &#x26; can save a lot of time. When working in Terminal or another command line app, you may want to set up an alias to make your workflows easier.\n{: .first-paragraph}</p>\n<p>To do this you’ll want to set up a <code class="language-text">.bash_profile</code>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Run <code class="language-text">vi ~/.bash_profile</code> in your command line app of choice, or [text editor of choice] ~/.bash_profile</li>\n<li>This will open up your <code class="language-text">bash profile</code> in <code class="language-text">vi</code> or your <code class="language-text">text editor</code> to be edited</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you’d like to use a text editor but don’t have one that opens instead of <code class="language-text">vi</code> checkout this <a href="//help.github.com/articles/associating-text-editors-with-git/">post</a></p>\n<p>Here’s a look at part of my <code class="language-text">.bash_profile</code>:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight" data-language="bash">\n      <pre class="language-bash"><code class="language-bash"><span class="token comment"># -------</span>\n<span class="token comment"># mySQL</span>\n<span class="token comment"># -------</span>\n<span class="token function">export</span> PATH<span class="token operator">=</span>/usr/local/mysql/bin:<span class="token variable">$PATH</span>\n\n<span class="token comment"># -------</span>\n<span class="token comment"># host setups</span>\n<span class="token comment"># -------</span>\n<span class="token function">alias</span> hosts<span class="token operator">=</span><span class="token string">"sublime /etc/hosts"</span>\n<span class="token function">alias</span> vhosts<span class="token operator">=</span><span class="token string">"sublime /etc/apache2/vhosts"</span></code></pre>\n      </div>',frontmatter:{featured_image:null,meta:"Creating Aliases on a Mac is an easy thing to do & can save a lot of time",title:"Creating Aliases on a Mac",date:"May 19, 2016",path:"/creating-aliases/"}}},pathContext:{}}}});
